                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>@Template[type:emanation|distance:30] @Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.Aura]{Aura} or @Template[type:emanation|distance:60] if the tormented is at 125 HP or lower.</p>\n<p>The psychic agony of a tormented spills into the world around them, inflicting murderous hallucinations replicating the tormented's last moments. A non-undead creature that ends its turn in the aura must succeed at a @Check[type:will|dc:32] save or for [[/br 1d4 #Dislocation Duration]]{1d4 rounds}, the creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Slowed]{Slowed 1}. While it has a condition from Tortured Gaze, a creature can't gain a new condition from the aura but can take damage from it again.</p>"
